00200 static inline void bnx2_skb_fill_page_desc(struct sk_buff *skb, int i,
00201                        struct page *page, int off, int size)
00202 {
00203 #if (LINUX_VERSION_CODE < 0x020600)
00204     skb_frag_t *frag = &skb_shinfo(skb)->frags[i];
00205 
00206     frag->page        = page;
00207     frag->page_offset     = off;
00208     frag->size        = size;
00209     skb_shinfo(skb)->nr_frags = i + 1;
00210 #else
00211     skb_fill_page_desc(skb, i, page, off, size);
00212 #endif
00213 }

00222 static inline void netif_tx_unlock(struct net_device *dev)
00223 {

00236 #ifdef OLD_NETIF
00237 static inline void netif_poll_disable(struct net_device *dev)
00238 {
00239     while (test_and_set_bit(__LINK_STATE_RX_SCHED, &dev->state)) {
00240         /* No hurry. */
00241         current->state = TASK_INTERRUPTIBLE;
00242         schedule_timeout(1);
00243     }
00244 }
00245 
00246 static inline void netif_poll_enable(struct net_device *dev)
00247 {
00248     clear_bit(__LINK_STATE_RX_SCHED, &dev->state);
00249 }
00250 
00251 static inline void netif_tx_disable(struct net_device *dev)
00252 {
00253     spin_lock_bh(&dev->xmit_lock);
00254     netif_stop_queue(dev);
00255     spin_unlock_bh(&dev->xmit_lock);
00256 }
00257 
00258 #endif

00406 static inline void bnx2_msleep(unsigned int msecs)
00407 {
00408 #if (LINUX_VERSION_CODE < 0x20607)
00409     current->state = TASK_UNINTERRUPTIBLE;
00410     schedule_timeout((msecs * HZ / 1000) + 1);
00411 #else
00412     msleep(msecs);
00413 #endif
00414 }
00415 
00416 static inline unsigned long bnx2_msleep_interruptible(unsigned int msecs)
00417 {
00418 #if (LINUX_VERSION_CODE < 0x20609)
00419     current->state = TASK_INTERRUPTIBLE;
00420     return schedule_timeout((msecs * HZ / 1000) + 1);
00421 #else
00422     return msleep_interruptible(msecs);
00423 #endif
00424 }

00432 #if defined (__VMKLNX__)
00433 
00436 static void *bcm_memmove(void *dest, const void *src, size_t count)
00437 {
00438     char *tmp;
00439     const char *s;
00440 
00441     if (dest <= src) {
00442         tmp = dest;
00443         s = src;
00444         while (count--)
00445             *tmp++ = *s++;
00446     } else {
00447         tmp = dest;
00448         tmp += count;
00449         s = src;
00450         s += count;
00451         while (count--)
00452             *--tmp = *--s;
00453     }
00454     return dest;
00455 }
00456 #else /* !defined (__VMKLNX__) */
00457 #define bcm_memmove memmove
00458 #endif /* defined (__VMKLNX__) */

07397 /* Use CPU native page size up to 16K for the ring sizes.  */
07398 #if (PAGE_SHIFT > 14)
07399 #define BCM_PAGE_BITS   14
07400 #else
07401 #define BCM_PAGE_BITS   PAGE_SHIFT
07402 #endif
07403 #define BCM_PAGE_SIZE   (1 << BCM_PAGE_BITS)
07404 
07405 #define TX_DESC_CNT  (BCM_PAGE_SIZE / sizeof(struct tx_bd))
07406 #define MAX_TX_DESC_CNT (TX_DESC_CNT - 1)
07407 
07408 #define MAX_RX_RINGS    16
07409 #define MAX_RX_PG_RINGS 64
07410 #define RX_DESC_CNT  (BCM_PAGE_SIZE / sizeof(struct rx_bd))
07411 #define MAX_RX_DESC_CNT (RX_DESC_CNT - 1)
07412 #define MAX_TOTAL_RX_DESC_CNT (MAX_RX_DESC_CNT * MAX_RX_RINGS)
07413 #define MAX_TOTAL_RX_PG_DESC_CNT (MAX_RX_DESC_CNT * MAX_RX_PG_RINGS)
07414 
07415 #define NEXT_TX_BD(x) (((x) & (MAX_TX_DESC_CNT - 1)) ==         \
07416         (MAX_TX_DESC_CNT - 1)) ?                \
07417     (x) + 2 : (x) + 1
07418 
07419 #define TX_RING_IDX(x) ((x) & MAX_TX_DESC_CNT)
07420 
07421 #define NEXT_RX_BD(x) (((x) & (MAX_RX_DESC_CNT - 1)) ==         \
07422         (MAX_RX_DESC_CNT - 1)) ?                \
07423     (x) + 2 : (x) + 1
07424 
07425 #define RX_RING_IDX(x) ((x) & bp->rx_max_ring_idx)
07426 #define RX_PG_RING_IDX(x) ((x) & bp->rx_max_pg_ring_idx)
07427 
07428 #define RX_RING(x) (((x) & ~MAX_RX_DESC_CNT) >> (BCM_PAGE_BITS - 4))
07429 #define RX_IDX(x) ((x) & MAX_RX_DESC_CNT)

07434 #define CTX_MASK                    (CTX_SIZE - 1)
07435 #define GET_CID_ADDR(_cid)          ((_cid) << CTX_SHIFT)
07436 #define GET_CID(_cid_addr)          ((_cid_addr) >> CTX_SHIFT)

07442 #define GET_PCID(_pcid_addr)        ((_pcid_addr) >> PHY_CTX_SHIFT)

07446 #define MB_KERNEL_CTX_MASK          (MB_KERNEL_CTX_SIZE - 1)
07447 #define MB_GET_CID_ADDR(_cid)       (0x10000 + ((_cid) << MB_KERNEL_CTX_SHIFT))

08001 /* This value (in milliseconds) determines the frequency of the driver
08002  * issuing the PULSE message code.  The firmware monitors this periodic
08003  * pulse to determine when to switch to an OS-absent mode. */
08004 #define BNX2_DRV_PULSE_PERIOD_MS                 250
08005 
08006 /* This value (in milliseconds) determines how long the driver should
08007  * wait for an acknowledgement from the firmware before timing out.  Once
08008  * the firmware has timed out, the driver will assume there is no firmware
08009  * running and there won't be any firmware-driver synchronization during a
08010  * driver reset. */
08011 #define BNX2_FW_ACK_TIME_OUT_MS         1000
